lass="size-full wp-image-3515886" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Scott Wilkinson a.k.a Yan of British Sea Power performs at Zavvi on January 7, 2008" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Scott-Yan-Wilkinson@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3515886" class="wp-caption-text"> Scott Wilkinson aka Yan of British Sea Power performs at Zavvi on January 7, 2008. CREDIT: Shirlaine Forrest/WireImage/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> The members found themselves wanting to drop the word &#39;British&#39; from their moniker due to misapprehensions from nationalists. The new name was introduced at the beginning of 2022.</p><p> “It just felt like a bit of a weird thing… that was colouring the meaning of songs and the world of our band in general,” <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/sea-power-british-gb-news-new-album-everything-was-forever-3161211">frontman Scott &#39;Yan&#39; Wilkinson told <em>NME</em></a> , discussing the change. “It always was a slightly complicated name, in a way, but it was meant to be something you&#39;d maybe think about, find fun and discuss, and the current climate just isn&#39;t good for things like that. There isn&#39;t open discussion and stuff. It&#39;s just people arguing, not listening and being weird.”</p><p> Since the transition into the name Sea Power, the band went on to release their latest album &#39;Everything Was Forever&#39; last February. Following its release, the LP went on to receive <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/sea-power-everything-was-forever-review-3158700">a four-star review from <em>NME</em></a> and put the band in <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sea-power-lead-close-race-this-week-number-one-3166183">a very close race to get their first UK Number One album</a> .</p><p> Back in 2019, the band also launched the debut edition of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sea-powers-krankenhaus-festival-completes-stacked-line-up-3262365">their annual Cumbrian festival, Krankenhaus.</a></p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sea-power-announce-do-you-like-rock-music-15th-anniversary-uk-tour-buy-tickets-3515882">Sea Power announce &#39;Do You Like Rock Music?&#39; 15th anniversary UK tour</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
